'''Kenny Easwaran''' is an American Indian philosopher and Professor of Philosophy at [[Texas A&M University]]. He is known for his expertise on [[epistemology]], [[decision theory]], [[mathematical logic]] and [[philosophy of mathematics]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Kenny Easwaran|url=https://philosophy.berkeley.edu/people/detail/56|website=[[UC Berkeley]]|accessdate=25 March 2018|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Kenny Easwaran|url=http://www.nasonline.org/programs/kavli-frontiers-of-science/frontiers-alumni/alumni-directory/kenny-easwaran.html|website=[[National Academy of Sciences]]|accessdate=25 March 2018}}</ref> Easwaran is an editor-in-chief of ''[[Journal of Philosophical Logic]]''. Two of his articles have been selected as among the "ten best" of their year by the ''[[Philosopher's Annual]]''.<ref>{{cite web|title=The Philosopher's Annual|url=http://www.pgrim.org/philosophersannual/past.html#v35|website=www.pgrim.org|accessdate=25 March 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=The Philosopher's Annual|url=http://www.pgrim.org/philosophersannual/past.html#v34|website=www.pgrim.org|accessdate=25 March 2018}}</ref>
